results.name: Numbers n which are the sum of 3 but no fewer nonzero fourth powers.
comment: Identical to A003337 for n = 1..87. - _Michael S. Branicky_, Mar 18 2021
link: Robert Israel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
maple: A:= sort(convert(F3 minus (F2 union F1), list)); # _Robert Israel_, Jul 24 2020
program: p1 = set(i**4 for i in range(1, int(lim**.25)+2) if i**4 <= lim)
p2 = set(a+b for a in p1 for b in p1 if a+b <= lim)
p3 = set(apb+c for apb in p2 for c in p1 if apb+c <= lim)
results.author: Arlin Anderson (starship1(AT)gmail.com)
